Some arithmetic operations in BigInteger can be improved by using `_addcarry_*` intrinsics. Taking [BigInteger.Add()](https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/blob/master/src/System.Private.CoreLib/shared/System/Number.BigInteger.cs#L393-L395) as an example:

```csharp
                while (smallIndex < smallLength)
                {
                    // *** could be improved by using _addcarry_u32 ***
                    ulong sum = carry + large._blocks[largeIndex] + small._blocks[smallIndex];
                    carry = sum >> 32;
                    // *** could be improved by using _addcarry_u32 ***

                    result._blocks[resultIndex] = (uint)(sum);

                    largeIndex++;
                    smallIndex++;
                    resultIndex++;
                }
```

Adding `_addcarry_*` series of intrinsics is the prerequisite to improve the performance of `BigInteger`.

